-- MOVES- Deutsche Bank, JPMorgan, Pictet, Lloyds 
-- 
-- Mon Nov 17, 2014 03:47PM EST
-- None



Nov 17 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Monday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

DEUTSCHE BANK AG <DBKGn.DE>  The bank's asset & wealth management unit said it has hired Munish Varma as head of structured solutions in its loans & deposits group. He was most recently global head of structured credit at Nomura. [ID:nL3N0T73RR]  LLOYDS BANKING GROUP PLC <LLOY.L> The bank's commercial banking unit named Miranda Zhao head of UK funds. Zhao joins from Erste Group Bank. [ID:nL3N0T74FJ]  TULLETT PREBON <TLPR.L> The interdealer broker said it had hired Carrie Heiss to the newly created role of global head of human resources as it reinforces controls on staff conduct in the wake of recent trading scandals. [ID:nL6N0T72EB]  PICTET ASSET MANAGEMENT The Swiss asset manager hired a team from Barings Asset Management to manage multi-asset funds. Percival Stanion, Andrew Cole and Shaniel Ramjee built multi-asset strategies at Barings. [ID:nL3N0T74QI]  JPMORGAN <JPM.N> Dag Skattum, the former global co-head of mergers and acquisitions at JP Morgan <JPM.N> who left the firm in 2007 to join private equity firm TPG [TPG.UL], is to rejoin the US bank as vice chairman of the Europe, Middle East and Africa region in January, according to a memo seen by IFR. [ID:nL6N0T7265]  CREDIT SUISSE AG <CSGN.VX> John Trousdale, vice chairman of global mergers and acquisitions at Credit Suisse, will leave the Swiss bank to join the new advisory firm headed by star investment banker Paul Taubman, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0T42M9]  PIONEER INVESTMENTS <CRDI.MI> The asset management arm of Italian bank UniCredit SpA named Craig Anzlovar as its fixed-income client portfolio manager. Anzlovar joins from Fidelity Investments. [ID:nL3N0T75TB]   PEMBERTON The asset management firm said Thomas Duetoft and John Doyle have joined the firm in London to strengthen its loan origination capability. [ID:nL6N0T73ND]  BESSEMER TRUST  The private wealth management and investment advisory firm appointed Grant Gardner as principal, head of estate administration and fiduciary counsel. The firm also appointed Steven Dwyer as senior vice president and real estate asset manager. [ID:nL3N0T75S2]  CLARION PARTNERS The real estate investment manager appointed Alan Rubenstein and Brian Collins as senior vice presidents in its asset management group. [ID:nL3N0T75TU]  FTI CONSULTING <FCN.N> The business advisory firm appointed Jonathan Tyler as managing director in the firm's strategic communications unit. [ID:nL3N0T748W]  CALASTONE